snippet.textDisplay:
My take on this quality song, 
portrayal of ' *_Struggle & Hope'_* 
 *Abdul Hanan* battles endless struggles with no clear *guiding star* as a *beacon of hope,*  while *Jaffer's insights offer a *glimmer of hopes,* reminder that strength always lies *hidden inside* the *heart* 
 ~Hats off to Coke studio for  knocking out of park again with  such a masterpiece &
 Thought provoking content~

Andar tere raaz kaye hai
Kudse jo mil paye ga
(Within you there are so many secrets, 
 Will you ever meet yourself? ) 

Oh yaara
Dil se jo sun paye ga
(Oh friend, 
Who can hear the heart's yearning) 

Na chor aas ki dur ko
Such tu samaj jaye ga
(Don't abandon the string of hope, 
This truth you'll understand) 

O yaara
Pir tu samal jaye ga
(Oh [dear] friend
Then [after all this] you'll feel a sense of consolation/comfort).
